I have enough information to make a well-informed pick. Let me synthesize what I've gathered:

**Duke:**
- KenPom #1, Torvik #1, AdjEM +39.17 — the nation's best team
- 31-2 record, #1 defense nationally (AdjDE 88.7/90.4), top-4 offense
- **Caleb Foster** (starting PG) is out for the "foreseeable future" after surgery — a significant injury
- Patrick Ngongba II returned for the ACC Tournament (per prior pick context)
- Won the ACC Tournament without Foster, though games were "a bit too close for comfort"

**Ohio State:**
- SRS 19.06 (27th nationally), ORtg 118.6 (35th), DRtg 108.2 (216th) — strong offense, weak defense
- 21-12 record, 8th in Big Ten, 12-8 conference record
- SOS ranked 16th nationally — genuinely battle-tested
- Hot late-season form (won 3 straight to close regular season)
- USA Today noted: "The Buckeyes are hot, and they can hang with premier teams"
- Prior pick noted NET #29, beat Purdue and Iowa late in the season

